{
  "id": "e41f877ead4d489d87186b80068fe908",
  "title": "The Flanking System",
  "description": "Fully Replicated Modular Flanking System For AI.",
  "longDescription": "<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v&#61;p8EwFSWDZAE\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong><u>Preview</u></strong></a></p><p><a href=\"https://1drv.ms/u/s!Av13Y2UmXSTQh7sUXZUINc_W6VCJFg?e&#61;Bfrep0\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong><u>Demo</u></strong></a></p><p>Example real world use case: This product is used in <a href=\"https://youtu.be/65RE3a3kn_g?si&#61;tXtbW8yv_vDPKDVq\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>Stencil of Judgement</strong></a>.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>PLEASE LEAVE A RATING IF YOU GET THIS PRODUCT. IT REALLY HELPS.</strong></p><p><strong>THANK YOU VERY MUCH FOR YOUR SUPPORT! </strong></p><p><br /></p><p>The Flanking System is a completely modular flanking system for AI characters. It is ready to use in multiplayer games and projects, as all required systems are replicated.</p><p><br /></p><p><u>System Design</u></p><ol><li>The AI can move, flank its current target, attack and defend.</li><li>The AI will strafe, whilst facing the player at all times. Because of this, the strafing should result in the AI “orbiting” the player, or moving around him in a circular manner.</li><li>The AI will move forward / backwards (closer / further from player) when needed.</li><li>The AI will attack using custom animation sets (each user can use their own animations).</li><li>The AI will have a set of attack animations that may vary from AI to AI.</li><li>The AI will enter a “defensive” stance, in which it defends against an attack.</li><li>The AI must have a method through which it can be “notified” that the player is attacking.</li><li>When the AI is notified of an incoming attack, we need to be able to tell the AI which direction it is coming from: Up, Bottom, Left, Right, Top-Left, Top-Right, Bottom-Left, Bottom-Right. Depending on which we notify him of, a specific “defense” animation plays from the animation set for defense.</li><li>If the AI is in the process of attacking, defensive mode should not be entered.</li><li>The AI will have an “Aggression” variable, a float from 0 to 1. The closer to 1 it is, the more frequently the AI will try to attack the player. The lower, the less frequently.</li></ol><p><br /></p><p>Ultimately, what we’re dealing with is simple AI that can move relative to the player, attack if not defending, and defend if not attacking depending on some variables (like“IsBeingAttacked?”, for example).</p>",
  "technicalDetails": "<p><strong>***Announcement: The Targeting System is currently free for the month! Get it </strong><a href=\"https://www.unrealengine.com/marketplace/en-US/product/the-targeting-system\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>here</strong></a><strong>.***</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>Features:</p><ul><li><strong>Multiplayer Ready</strong></li><li>AI Behavior Tree</li><li>Flanking System</li><li>Attacks</li><li>Defense</li><li>Custom Targeting System</li><li>AI Perception</li><li>EQS (Environment Querying System)</li><li>Notifies that can be applied to <strong>ANY</strong> animation sequence or montage</li><li><strong>Modular component that holds all the parameters used by the AI and player</strong></li><li><strong>Additive Animation Setup</strong></li><li><strong>Extensively documented and commented, with several tooltips on some variables</strong></li><li><strong>Aggression Parameter For AI</strong></li><li>Customizable Animation Montages</li><li>Attack Types Enumeration</li></ul><p>Number of Blueprints: 27</p><p>Input: (Keyboard: Press &#34;F&#34; To Attack as the player))</p><p><strong>Network Replicated: (Yes)</strong></p><p>Supported Development Platforms: (PC, Mobile)</p><p>Supported Target Build Platforms: (PC, Mobile)</p><p><a href=\"https://www.evernote.com/l/AhTyrlbacYhMv6IC1egtz0DhVZSesIg2qjI/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Documentation</a></p><p><br /></p><p><u>Credits:</u></p><p>Designed by: Alek Sinn</p><p>Developed by: Ibrahim Akinde</p><p><br /></p><p><u>Please leave a rating and/or review. It helps!</u></p>",
